@startuml
title Sequence - Signup Flow Target V1

skinparam shadowing false

actor "RegisterUserTest\n(Target V1 View)" as TEST
participant "FakeDataGenerator" as FDG
participant "UserDataBuilder" as UDB
participant "HomePage" as HP
participant "LoginPage" as LP
participant "SignupFlow" as SF
participant "SignupPage" as SP
participant "AccountCreatedPage" as ACP
participant "StateStore" as SS
participant "UserApiService" as UAS
participant "Automation Exercise UI" as UI
participant "Automation Exercise API" as API

TEST -> FDG : timestamp()
TEST -> UDB : aUser().withName(...)\n.withPassword(...).build()
UDB --> TEST : User

TEST -> HP : open()
HP -> UI : GET /
UI --> HP : home page DOM
TEST -> HP : openLoginPage()
HP --> TEST : LoginPage

TEST -> SF : register(user)
SF -> LP : enterSignupName(user.name)
SF -> LP : enterSignupEmail(user.email)
SF -> LP : startSignup()
LP -> UI : submit signup start
UI --> SP : signup form loaded
SF -> SP : fillAccountDetails(user)
SF -> SP : submitAccountCreation()
SP -> UI : submit account form
UI --> ACP : account created page
SF --> TEST : AccountCreatedPage

TEST -> ACP : continueToHomePage()
ACP -> UI : continue navigation
UI --> HP : logged-in home page
TEST -> SS : put("registeredUserEmail", user.email)

opt Best-effort cleanup
  TEST -> UAS : deleteUser(user.email, user.password)
  UAS -> API : DELETE /api/deleteAccount
  API --> UAS : ApiResponse
end

note right of SS
State persistence is shown as the
target V1 handoff model. The current
registration test already cleans up
through UserApiService but does not
yet rely on StateStore for the flow.
end note

@enduml
